==Description== <!--T:3-->

<!--T:4-->
The [[Image:Part_ToleranceSet.svg|24px]] '''Part ToleranceSet''' command creates a parametric copy of selected objects with all contained tolerances set to at least a certain minimum value. The created object behaves like a compound if multiple objects are selected/added to the feature, or as a single shape if only one object is selected.

<!--T:5-->
Tolerances affect subsequent OCCT functions such as boolean operations. Tolerances of sub-shapes can be inspected with the help of [[PartDesign_SubShapeBinder|Subshapebinders]] and the [[Part_CheckGeometry|Check Geometry]] command.

==Usage== <!--T:6-->

<!--T:7-->
# Select one or more objects.
# Select the {{MenuCommand|Part → Compound → [[Image:Part_ToleranceSet.svg|16px]] Set Tolerance}} option from the menu.
# A Tolerance object is created and the original object hidden.

==Properties== <!--T:8-->

<!--T:9-->
{{Properties_Title|Tolerance Set}}

<!--T:10-->
*{{PropertyData|Objects}}: Objects to have tolerance adjusted.
*{{PropertyData|Refine}}: If true, refinement of the resulting shape is enabled.
*{{PropertyData|max Tolerance}}: Sets the maximum tolerance for the shape and all subshapes (if any).
*{{PropertyData|min Tolerance}}: Sets the minimum tolerance for the shape and all subshapes (if any).


